<title>NETHERLANDS: BAM maintains 1997 earnings forecast.</title>
<headline>BAM maintains 1997 earnings forecast.</headline>
<dateline>AMSTERDAM 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dutch builder BAM said on Friday it maintained its earlier forecast it would achieve a net profit of at least 20 million guilders in 1997.</p>
<p>BAM said earlier on Friday it had broken off merger talks with sector companion Wilma.</p>
<p>BAM said it had set the stock alternative to its 1996 dividend at 2.5 percent in shares against the general reserve, plus a cash payment of 2.30 guilders.</p>
<p>In April, BAM announced it would pay a 1996 cash dividend of 5.25 guilders. It said at the time that the final payment could be taken up in cash or in new shares.</p>
